[p][img src="{STEAM_CLAN_IMAGE}/9703436/57dc029fc7d4e07f0b73b008c355eb9a44555ca8.png"][/img][/p][p][i]by PDX-Loke[/i][/p][p][/p][p]Hello all,[/p][p][/p][p align="start"]We have a patch ready for you, resolving another set of gameplay issues as well as a few more crashes.
4.1.3 is now available for download via Steam, GOG, and MS. (4.1.2 beta was not promoted to a main branch release)[/p][p][/p][p align="start"]Please find the patch notes below.[/p][h1]Stellaris 4.1.3 patch notes[/h1][list][*][p]Fixed default leader tiers not being loaded properly from a savegame, sometimes causing Psionic traits to be lost[/p][/*][*][p]Removed invalid armies from savefiles after planet occupation issues[/p][list][*][p]Fix versus the open beta: Stop removing allied armies from planets not in combat[/p][/*][/list][/*][*][p]Teeth of the Eater no longer use naval capacity when merged into fleets.[/p][/*][*][p]Made Natural Design mutually exclusive with Shroud Civic and Origin combinations that would prevent ascension[/p][/*][*][p]Raiding stance will abduct Pre-FTL pops again[/p][/*][*][p]Colonist jobs are now available for Tankbound species[/p][/*][*][p]Fixed ground battles finishing instantly[/p][/*][*][p]Death Cult sacrifices are now once again available at the start of the game[/p][/*][*][p]Death Cult sacrifices now require at least 100 Mortal Initiates[/p][/*][*][p]The tankbound Toxoid portrait now counts as potentially having a big brain[/p][/*][*][p]Secondary empire color is now used for country borders[/p][/*][*][p]The reduction in planetary district capacity by deposits granted by the Composer of Strands is negated if you have a covenant with them or are forging your own path. These planetary deposits have additional effects in this case as well.[/p][/*][*][p]Fixed crash in the planet view demographics tab[/p][/*][*][p]Fixed crash that could occur in the Shroud view[/p][/*][*][p]Fix for leaders not gaining Psionic traits when completing Psionic ascension[/p][/*][/list][p align="start"]Work is ongoing and we have a more extensive patch in progress carrying wider reaching fixes and balance updates. Stay attuned for that next week.[/p]